df1g

I feel that the k-means results are not useful.

If we look at the figure, we will see that the clustering is based almost exclusively on the alcohol. The reason this happens I assume, is that ra has largest numerical values. K-means is based on Euclidean distances and is highly sensitive to normalization. Having one variable that is on a much larger scale than all the others, can completely bias the clustering.

I think we can safely conclude that this particular analysis is useless.

And enough data is not present for k=2
